An Act relating to prisons and reformatories;
creating the Prison Acquisition Revolving Fund;
establishing revolving fund characteristics; deeming
certain deposits appropriated; authorizing
expenditure for certain purpose; establishing budget
and expenditure limits and requirements; amending 57
O.S. 2021, Section 509, as last amended by Section 1,
Chapter 22, O.S.L. 2023 (57 O.S. Supp. 2024, Section
509), which relates to penal institutions; adding to
and updating the list of facilities the Department of
Corrections is authorized to maintain; providing for
codification; and declaring an emergency.
SUBJECT: Prisons and reformatories
BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:

Section 2:
SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 509A of Title 57, unless there
is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
There is hereby created in the State Treasury a revolving fund
for the Department of Corrections to be designated the "Prison
Acquisition Revolving Fund". The fund shall be a continuing fund,
not subject to fiscal year limitations, and shall consist of all
monies designated for deposit by law. All monies accruing to the
credit of said fund are hereby appropriated and may be budgeted and
expended by the Department for the purpose of, on behalf of the
state, completing a purchase of a prison including associated
property and equipment from a private prison contractor.
Expenditures from said fund shall be made upon warrants issued by
the State Treasurer against claims filed as prescribed by law with
the Director of the Office of Management and Enterprise Services for
approval and payment.

